A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Tricia Gephardt; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Tricia Gephardt has demonstrated an unwavering commitment to service,
3 leadership, and community engagement through her extensive volunteer work and
4 professional experience; and
5 WHEREAS, she holds a Bachelor of Arts in government from Georgetown University,
6 where she cultivated a deep understanding of public service and civic responsibility; and
7 WHEREAS, Tricia began her career in public service by working on Capitol Hill in
8 Washington, D.C., for the House Majority Leader, gaining invaluable experience in
9 government operations and legislative affairs; and
10 WHEREAS, she has further contributed to the democratic process by lending her talents to
11 state and local political campaigns in Georgia, helping to foster civic engagement and
12 informed participation in the electoral process; and
