13 WHEREAS, as a dedicated stay-at-home mother, she has continued to lead and serve,
14 demonstrating the profound impact of volunteerism on the strength and well-being of our
15 communities; and
16 WHEREAS, Tricia has made significant contributions to education and youth development,
17 serving as the Parents' Association president at Holy Innocents' Episcopal School and as an
18 advisory council member for Horizons Atlanta, where she worked to enhance educational
19 opportunities for children, in addition to her longtime commitment to supporting the
20 nonprofit CURE, which is dedicated to conquering childhood cancer; and
21 WHEREAS, her commitment to civic engagement led her to found The Postcard Project, a
22 grassroots initiative designed to foster meaningful dialogue, increase voter participation, and
23 encourage community involvement; and
24 WHEREAS, Tricia's tireless efforts exemplify the highest ideals of service and civic
25 leadership, inspiring others to take an active role in strengthening their communities.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 recognize and commend Tricia Gephardt for her dedication to public service, her leadership
28 in education and community engagement, and her enduring contributions to the State of
29 Georgia.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Tricia Gephardt.
